description.narrative: This recently-launched USAID program is part of a larger U.S.~government effort to promote democratic representative governance in Venezuela and similar to democracy and governance support in various countries around the world. The program responds to increasing government control over news and information available on broadcast media and seeks to increase the availability of independent news to lower-income Venezuelans, who generally lack ongoing, fast Internet access. This program will emphasize research to ensure that media outlets and the Venezuelan public have data-driven, gender-disaggregated, information on media consumption patterns among lower-income segments of Venezuela's population. The program will also support Venezuelan journalist networks producing independent content for the target audiences.
